# Curated for a 2001-era Win32/DirectX codebase being ported to modern
# platforms. Default clang-tidy is tuned for idiomatic modern C++ and would
# be almost entirely noise here (naming conventions, modernize-* rewrites of
# perfectly fine legacy code, etc.) — this config keeps the checks that find
# real bugs and drops the ones that just complain about house style.
#
# Deliberately kept:
# - bugprone-narrowing-conversions: this project's whole ARM64 port has been
#   full of `long`/`DWORD`/pointer-truncation bugs (see ENGINEERING_LOG.md) —
#   this is exactly the class of thing worth catching automatically.
# - clang-analyzer-*: real static-analysis bug detection (leaks, null derefs,
#   use-after-free), always worth the noise.
# - portability-*: directly relevant — this project targets macOS/Linux/
#   Windows from one codebase.
#
# Deliberately dropped:
# - modernize-*: would push wholesale rewrites of vendored/legacy code
#   (raw loops, C-style casts, NULL, etc.) that isn't this project's to
#   rewrite wholesale.
# - readability-*, google-*, llvm-*, fuchsia-*, altera-*, objc-*: house-style
#   opinions that don't fit a ported legacy codebase.
# - cppcoreguidelines-*: mostly overlaps with modernize-* concerns here.
# - bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters: near-100% false positive rate on
#   any function with 2+ same-type params — not useful signal.
# - bugprone-reserved-identifier: this codebase's whole porting-shim layer
#   deliberately defines __stdcall/__cdecl/_GUID/etc. to match the Win32
#   names the vendored original source expects — that's the point, not a
#   bug. Measured 32 hits on a single file's includes, all of this kind.
# - performance-enum-size: micro-optimization nitpick (shrink an enum's
#   underlying type), not a bug; 41 hits on one file, zero of them
#   actionable. Pure noise-to-signal loss.
# - portability-avoid-pragma-once: `#pragma once` is universally supported
#   by every compiler this project targets; this check is for portability
#   to compilers nobody's shipping this on.

Checks: >
  -*,
  bugprone-*,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,
  -bugprone-reserved-identifier,
  clang-analyzer-*,
  portability-*,
  -portability-avoid-pragma-once,
  performance-*,
  -performance-enum-size

WarningsAsErrors: ''

# Only this project's own headers — not system/Homebrew/Vulkan SDK headers,
# and not vendored third-party code (thirdparty/pl_mpeg).
HeaderFilterRegex: '(^|/)(code|mclib|GameOS|Viewer|data_tools|text_tool|tools|gui|misc|res)/.*\.(h|hpp)$'

FormatStyle: none
